Program: Discovery
Title: Dark matter
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxsg
Last Broadcast Date: 01 May 2001
Why cosmologists are confused over the existence and influence of dark matter. The true universe is dark, with at least 90 per cent of the matter of a galaxy not able to reflect light. What is most of the universe made of? This is a question that baffles cosmologists.